	   <tr><td colspan=2>This probably wouldn't be one of the things you'd make for profit.<br><br>Remember, the fail rate on velious tailored stuff is insane.  At 160ish skill -- where you can no longer raise skill with cheap recipies like Wu's -- you have a 3-5% success rate.  Supposedly, it increases to 5-10% or better around 200 skill, but that takes an incredible amount of work...<br><br>Think about how much it would cost, on average, to make one of these with a 5% success rate (optimistic, for most)...that's 20 combines -- 80 rubies, 120 ice burrower silks.  The rubies themselves, IIRC gem prices, would cost over 10k.<br><br>Would this cloak sell for an amount justifying that much cost and effort?  I don't know for certain...would probably depend on how much value is placed on charisma.  Few casters that would pay several kpp for an item have trouble reaching 200 int.<br>&nbsp;<br>Aatudien of Elddar Caste, 57 necro, Lanys T'Vyl</td></tr>
